---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-vietnam', text: 'Leaving Vietnamese Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'language-support', text: 'Vietnamese Language Support', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Asia Insurance', href: '/best/asia-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'vietnameseSupport', header: 'Vietnamese Support' },
  { key: 'usNetwork', header: 'US Network' },
  { key: 'vietnamCoverage', header: 'Vietnam Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', vietnameseSupport: 'Limited', usNetwork: 'Strong', vietnamCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$175/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', vietnameseSupport: 'Limited', usNetwork: 'Excellent', vietnamCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$195/mo' },
  { provider: 'Pacific Cross Vietnam', vietnameseSupport: 'Full', usNetwork: 'Limited', vietnamCoverage: 'Included', price: '$140/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bao Viet', vietnameseSupport: 'Full', usNetwork: 'Limited', vietnamCoverage: 'Included', price: '$100/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', vietnameseSupport: 'Limited', usNetwork: 'Good', vietnamCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$170/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Vietnamese Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Vietnamese expats. Find coverage for the US, Europe, and other destinations with Vietnamese language support options."
  headline="Best Insurance for Vietnamese Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Vietnamese communities abroad are growing rapidly. Here's how to stay protected whether you're in the US, Europe, or elsewhere."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/vietnamese-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Vietnamese expats are found in significant numbers in the US, France, Germany, Australia, and other countries. The US has the largest Vietnamese diaspora. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Vietnamese expats heading to the US or Europe. Strong networks, comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Top-tier service quality.</li>
    <li><strong>Pacific Cross Vietnam:</strong> Vietnam-based with international coverage. Full Vietnamese support, includes Vietnam.</li>
    <li><strong>Bao Viet:</strong> Major Vietnamese insurer with some international options. Familiar brand, Vietnamese service.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="US Healthcare Reality"
    description="The US has the largest Vietnamese community outside Vietnam. US healthcare costs are extreme—a hospital stay can cost $50,000-$200,000+. Comprehensive insurance is essential, not optional."
    buttonText="Get US Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-vietnam">Leaving Vietnamese Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Vietnam has a social health insurance system. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Social Health Insurance (BHYT)</h3>
  <p>
    Vietnam's compulsory social health insurance covers employed workers and others. Coverage is tied to Vietnamese residence and employment. When you leave Vietnam, this coverage effectively ends for international purposes.
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage Limitations</h3>
  <p>
    Vietnamese social insurance provides no meaningful international coverage. Emergency treatment abroad is not covered. You need dedicated international insurance for any healthcare needs outside Vietnam.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Vietnamese Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Vietnamese companies (Bao Viet, Prudential Vietnam, Manulife Vietnam) may offer limited international emergency coverage. For long-term stays abroad, dedicated international coverage is essential.
  </p>

  <h3>Returning for Treatment</h3>
  <p>
    Some Vietnamese expats return to Vietnam for medical treatment due to lower costs. International insurance that includes Vietnam coverage allows this flexibility. Consider this when choosing your plan.
  </p>

  <h2 id="language-support">Vietnamese Language Support</h2>
  <p>
    Access to Vietnamese-language support can be important during medical emergencies:
  </p>

  <h3>What to Look For</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Vietnamese-speaking customer service</li>
    <li>Claims support in Vietnamese</li>
    <li>Assistance finding Vietnamese-speaking doctors abroad</li>
    <li>Vietnamese-language documentation if needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Provider Availability</h3>
  <p>
    Vietnamese insurers (Pacific Cross Vietnam, Bao Viet) offer full Vietnamese service. International insurers like Cigna and Bupa have limited Vietnamese capability—English is typically required. Consider your language comfort when choosing.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Vietnamese Doctors Abroad</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Cities with large Vietnamese communities (Orange County, Houston, San Jose, Paris) often have Vietnamese-speaking doctors. Your insurer covers any qualified physician, and community networks can help locate familiar providers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Vietnamese expats in the US—the most common destination. Strong US networks are critical given American healthcare costs. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 English service. Vietnam coverage can be added for visits home or medical tourism.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Vietnamese expats in the US who want reliable coverage with strong networks.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Service quality is outstanding—fast claims, comprehensive benefits including mental health and maternity.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Best for professionals who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Vietnamese professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>Pacific Cross Vietnam</h3>
  <p>
    Pacific Cross Vietnam offers international products for Vietnamese citizens abroad. Full Vietnamese-language support, familiar processes, Vietnam coverage included automatically.
  </p>

  <p>
    International networks are adequate, strongest in Asia. Good option for those prioritizing Vietnamese service.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Vietnamese expats who prefer Vietnamese-language service and seamless Vietnam coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Bao Viet</h3>
  <p>
    Bao Viet is Vietnam's largest insurer (state-owned) and offers some international products. Full Vietnamese service, familiar brand, Vietnam coverage included. International networks are limited compared to global insurers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Vietnamese expats who want familiar Vietnamese service and primarily need Vietnam coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe and adequate coverage elsewhere. Good option for Vietnamese expats in European destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Vietnamese expats in Europe seeking good value.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Balance global network strength against Vietnamese-language support based on your comfort level and destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs vary by destination. Here's what Vietnamese expats should consider:
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Vietnamese diaspora, especially in California (Orange County, San Jose), Texas (Houston), and other states. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. Many Vietnamese-speaking doctors in Vietnamese communities.
  </p>

  <h3>France</h3>
  <p>
    Historical connections mean a significant Vietnamese community, especially in Paris. French healthcare is excellent but requires proper enrollment. International insurance covers transition periods and provides additional options.
  </p>

  <h3>Australia</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Vietnamese community, especially in Sydney and Melbourne. Medicare covers permanent residents after waiting period. International insurance covers the gap and supplements public healthcare.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Vietnamese community, especially in Berlin and eastern Germany. German healthcare requires enrollment in the local system. International insurance covers transitions.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does Vietnamese insurance cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Vietnamese social insurance provides no international coverage. Private Vietnamese policies have very limited international coverage. You need dedicated international health insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can I return to Vietnam for treatment?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes, if your international policy includes Vietnam coverage. Many Vietnamese expats use this option for non-emergency care due to lower costs and language comfort.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Vietnamese language support important?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Depends on your English comfort level. In medical emergencies, native language support reduces stress. Consider your situation when choosing providers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Vietnam visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Vietnamese insurers include it automatically. International insurers offer Vietnam as a coverage region. Confirm details with your chosen provider.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Pacific Cross or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Pacific Cross offers Vietnamese service and includes Vietnam. Cigna has stronger global networks, especially in the US. Choose based on destination and language preference.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Are there Vietnamese doctors in the US?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes, especially in Orange County, Houston, San Jose, and other cities with large Vietnamese communities. Community networks can help find Vietnamese-speaking providers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Vietnamese expats need comprehensive international insurance—Vietnamese coverage doesn't extend abroad. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for reliable US coverage. <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage for those wanting the best.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Pacific Cross Vietnam</strong> suits those who prefer Vietnamese-language service and included Vietnam coverage. <strong>Bao Viet</strong> works for those prioritizing familiar Vietnamese service.
  </p>

  <p>
    Consider your destination's healthcare costs—US coverage especially requires strong networks. Balance network strength against language support based on your comfort level.
  </p>

</PageShell>
